OL,3,CKirkup 'disappointed' with response to
OL,4,Cmedical negligence claims
OL,6,FThe chairman of an inquiry into
OL,7,Fmaternity failings in Kent has said he
OL,8,Fis "disappointed" with the approach
OL,9,Fauthorities are taking in resolving
OL,10,Fsome clinical negligence claims by
OL,11,Faffected families.
OL,13,FDr Bill Kirkup's 2022 report into
OL,14,Fmaternity services at East Kent
OL,15,FHospitals found that if women and
OL,16,Fbabies had received nationally
OL,17,Frecognised standards of care then 45
OL,18,Fbabies may have survived, 12 babies
OL,19,Fmay not have suffered brain injury and
OL,20,F23 women who died or were injured
OL,21,Fcould have had a different outcome.
OL,26,@pD@DOUpD@QO]
